TO AMEND THE SUBSTITUTE AMENDMENT TO H.R. 23673, BY ELIMINATING THE CLAUSE WHICH PROVIDES THAT IT SHALL BE A CRIMINAL OFFENSE TO DISSUADE OR ATTEMPT TO DISSUADE ANY PERSON FROM TAKING EMPLOYMENT ON ANY VESSEL, OR FROM REMAINING IN THE SERVICE OF ANY VESSEL, OR TO DISOBEY ANY LAWFUL ORDER OF HIS SUPERIORS.

TO AMEND AN AMENDMENT TO H.R. 23673, BY PROVIDING THAT A SEAMEN 1 SHALL BE ENTITLED TO THE RATING OF EFFICIENT LIFEBOAT HAND WHO HAS SHOWN BY PRACTICAL TEST TO THE SATISFACTION OF THE BOARD OF LORD INSPECTORS THAT HE IS QUALIFIED TO PERFORM ANY DUTY REFERRED IN THE LAUNCHING AND HANDLING OF LIFEBOATS.  (P. 4586-2)
TO AMEND H.R. 23673, BY PROVIDING THAT THE ACT APPLY ONLY TO VESSELS NAVIGATING RIVERS EXCLUSIVELY.  (P. 4586-1)

TO AMEND A SUBSTITUTE AMENDMENT TO H.R. 23673, BY INCLUDING IN THE REGULATIONS GOVERNING MERCHANT VESSELS OF THE U.S., VESSELS OF LESS THAN 300 GROSS TONS, AND VESSELS WHOSE REGULAR SCHEDULE BETWEEN TERMINAL PORTS DOES NOT EXCEED TWELVE HOURS.  (P. 4563-2)
TO AMEND AN AMENDMENT TO H.R. 23673, BY INCLUDING WITHIN THE TERMS AND PROVISIONS OF THIS ACT VESSELS CARRYING PASSENGERS FOR HIRE.  (P. 4588-1)
TO ADJOURN.

TO CONSIDER S. 5382, WITH HOUSE AMENDMENTS, A BILL TO PROVIDE AN EXCLUSIVE REMEDY AND COMPENSATION FOR ACCIDENTAL INJURIES, RESULTING IN DISABILITY OR DEATH, TO EMPLOYEES OF COMMON CARRIERS BY RAILROADS ENGAGED IN THE INTERSTATE OR FOREIGN COMMERCE, OR IN THE DISTRICT OF COLUMBIA AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES.  (P. 4674-1)
TO AGREE TO THE CONFERENCE REPORT ON H.R. 27148, (37 STAT. 791, 3-4-13), A BILL MAKING APPROPRIATION FOR THE SERVICE OF THE POST OFFICE DEPARTMENT FOR FISCAL 1914.  (P. 4693-1)

TO TABLE THE REPORT OF THE CONFERENCE COMMITTEE ON H.R. 28766, (37 STAT. 866, 3-4-13), A BILL TO LIMIT THE COST OF CERTAIN BUILDING TO AUTHORIZE THE EMPLOYMENT, EXTENSION, REMODELLING AND IMPROVEMENT OF CERTAIN PUBLIC BUILDINGS, TO AUTHORIZE THE ERECTION AND COMPLETION OF PUBLIC BUILDINGS, TO AUTHORIZE THE PURCHASE OF SITES FOR PUBLIC BUILDINGS, AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES. TO AGREE TO THE CONFERENCE REPORT ON H.R. 28766, (37 STAT. 866, 3-4-13), A BILL TO INCREASE THE LIMIT COST OF CERTAIN BUILDINGS; TO AUTHORIZE THE ENLARGEMENT, EXTENSION, REMODELING, OR IMPROVEMENT OF CERTAIN PUBLIC BUILDINGS; TO AUTHORIZE THE ERECTION AND COMPLETION OF PUBLIC BUILDINGS TO AUTHORIZE THE PURCHASE OF SITES FOR PUBLIC BUILDINGS.
